  <summary date="2020-08-20T14:24:48Z" status="Introduced in House">Consumer Financial Protection Commission Act

This bill removes the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau from the Federal Reserve System, converts the bureau into an independent commission, and modifies its leadership structure.&#160;Specifically, the bill eliminates the positions of director and deputy director and establishes a five-person commission appointed by the President and confirmed by the Senate.</summary>
